                        |  2 expecting Grand Theft Auto with horses will be rather baffled by this slow-paced, sumptuous, character-driven Old West historical drama, in which you spend probably 60% of your time simply riding around the American wilderness. There&rsquo;s action too, in the form of shootouts, train robberies and frequent thrilling escapes on horseback, but these flashes of excitement punctuate a game that is largely about just being somewhere; about hunting, fishing and having long conversations on cross-country rides or around a campfire. In a mad fit of indulgence, Rockstar Games &ndash; the creators of Grand Theft Auto and one of the most successful game developers in the world &ndash; appears to have spent seven years and hundreds of millions creating the video game equivalent of Deadwood.
                    p.css-1x4bywk
                        | This is a story &ndash; a collection of stories, really &ndash; about the decline of a way of life, as a small gang of outlaws tries ever harder to outrun the inexorable advance of American modernity, as well as the enemies and lawmen they have antagonised along the way. The player&rsquo;s character, Arthur Morgan, is one of a small central cast assembled around gang leader Dutch Van der Linde, a classic western outlaw who fancies himself as a freedom fighter rather than a base criminal. The game takes in encounters with con men, warring Southern estates, rival gangs and a vivid array of incidental characters shaping turn-of-the-century America, touching upon race and women&rsquo;s suffrage, but keeping the overarching narrative focused on the Van der Linde band and the relationships within it.
